com.example.meditrackr.models.record

Class Geolocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.meditrackr.models.record.Geolocation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Geolocation
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Geolocation: represents a geolocation point on a map by tracking latitude, longitude, and a string address name of the geolocation for a particular record. Getters and setters can be used to retrieve or modify any of the geolocation attributes.
